article.description: Alison Lacey had 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead Iowa State (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 75-59 victory over Prairie View A&M on Friday in the Waikiki Beach Marriott Classic.
article.headline: No. 22 Iowa State moves to 4-0 behind Lacey's double-double
article.linkText: Lacey's double-double lifts Iowa State to victory
article.story:
HONOLULU --  Alison Lacey had 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead Iowa State (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 75-59 victory over Prairie View A&M on Friday in the Waikiki Beach Marriott Classic.

Kelsey Bolte added 12 points for the Cyclones, who improved to 4-0 for the first time since 2001-02 when they won their first 12 games of the season.

Aminata Dieye's layup with 3:13 left narrowed Iowa State's lead to 67-56, but Lacey scored five points in the final 2 minutes to put it out of reach.

Gaeti Werema and Chari Smith each had 12 points for the Lady Panthers (1-4).
